Place the folder 'pi' in the home directory of the user pi (i.e. /home/pi/) on the RaspberryPi
Place the folder 'beaglebone' in the home directory of the user debian (/home/debian/) on the Beaglebone

These scripts are launched at boot time by rc.local on both the RPi and BB.

If you are setting this up on a fresh install, you will need to modify /etc/rc.local to launch
launch these scripts.  If you have a provided pre-confgured SD card, this will have been done.

You will need to set up the paths to your projects bin folder in this script for the script to 
properly work.

